description: Set out bowls of seasoned ground beef, corn chips, and all the fixings and let your guests and family members design their own taco salads at the table. Kids love it.

title: Broccoli Slaw with Spicy Dressing
description: Taste a broccoli slaw dressing that's creamy, spicy, sweet, and tangy, with mayonnaise, juicy lime, sugar, chili powder, cumin, and cayenne.

title: Grilled Chicken Fajita Salad
description: Chicken strips are grilled with peppers and onions and served over lettuce in this easy recipe for a hearty fajita salad.

title: Italian Taco Salad
description: Browned ground beef is tossed with two kinds of cheese, crushed tortilla chips, and mixed salad greens, and topped with zesty Italian dressing.

title: Taco Pasta Salad with French Dressing
description: This taco pasta salad has all the makings of a potluck crowd-pleaser, from the ground beef and rotini to the lettuce, tomato, and crushed Doritos® that top it all off.

title: Grandma's Easy Turkey Taco Salad
description: Seasoned ground turkey is tossed with black beans, lettuce, tomato, tortilla chips, and dressing.

title: Turkey Taco Salad
description: Lots of flavors and textures in this hearty turkey salad that is also low-fat. The dressing is zesty - fat-free mayonnaise, lemon juice, vinegar, and taco sauce. For a bit of crunch, tortilla chips are folded into the salad at the last minute.

title: Quick Turkey Taco Salad
description: Cook ground turkey with prepared taco seasoning and bell pepper to put atop piles of salad greens and tortilla chips to make a quick and easy taco salad.

title: Taco Bean Salad
description: This filling taco bean salad is made with ground beef, four types of beans, and a homemade dressing.

title: Low-Fat Taco Salad
description: Enjoy this tasty taco salad made with vegetarian crumbles, low-fat Cheddar cheese, and lettuce as a great alternative to traditional taco salad.

title: Mom's Hot Mexican Salad
description: Just like eating a beef taco without the tortilla. It's got lots of cumin and green chilies mixed into the ground beef and other goodies. And it 's served hot so the cheese is all melted and wonderful.

title: Dana's Taco Salad
description: Ground turkey and lentils are cooked with taco seasoning before being tossed with lettuce, avocado, tomatoes, olives and kidney beans for a delicious take on taco salad.

title: Healthier Taco Salad
description: A surefire kid pleaser, this taco salad with yummy seasoned ground beef, baked tortilla chips, low-fat Cheddar cheese, and salsa is a healthier back-to-school lunch option.

title: Fish Taco Salad
description: Crispy fish fillets sit atop fresh vegetables in this fish taco salad that's ideal if you're cutting back on carbs.

title: Vegetarian Taco Salad
description: Katherine's Famous Vegetarian Taco Salad; layered, so chips don't get soggy! Top with sour cream or guacamole if you'd like. We like to make our own bowls for individual tastes.

title: Rio Grande Especial
description: Use this recipe to make flavorful ground beef for use in your favorite Mexican food items, such as tacos, taco salads, or burritos.

title: Taco Salad
description: This taco salad is a quick and easy warm salad made with chili beans, spicy ground beef, French dressing, lettuce, salsa, cheese, and tortilla chips.

title: Classic Chicken Caesar Salad
description: A classic recipe for a reason, this chicken Caesar salad is delicious and satisfying. Crunchy romaine, creamy dressing, tender chicken and savoury cheese come together for a tasty favourite.

title: Classic Restaurant Caesar Salad
description: This recipe for the original Caesar salad is surprisingly easy and quick to make with homemade dressing for a dish with restaurant-quality flavor.

title: The Last Caesar Salad Recipe You'll Ever Need
description: This is a classic creamy Caesar salad dressing that's perfect for a salad or for dipping vegetables. To serve, toss with chopped romaine in a salad bowl and shave Parmesan cheese on top of salad; season with salt, black pepper, and a squeeze of fresh lemon juice.

title: Caesar Salad I
description: The hardest thing about making a Caesar salad is getting the dressing right. This does, coddled egg and all.

title: Classic Caesar Salad with Homemade Croutons
description: Homemade croutons and cold, crunchy romaine are tossed in a briny, rich Caesar dressing, delivering a restaurant-quality salad in the comfort of your home.

title: Easy and Fast Cajun Chicken Caesar Salad
description: This blackened chicken Caesar salad recipe adds tender strips of Cajun-spiced chicken for a spicy spin on a classic salad. Easy and tasty!

title: Chicken Caesar Salad on a Stick
description: Chicken Caesar salad on a stick is a quick and easy version of the classic Caesar salad and perfect for parties.

title: Shaved Brussels Sprouts Caesar Salad
description: Creamy, tangy, and crunchy, our Brussels sprouts Caesar salad starts with the raw crispiness of Brussels sprouts smothered in Caesar dressing, and topped with bacon and croutons.

title: Kale Caesar Salad
description: Substitute kale for romaine salad in this otherwise classic Caesar salad topped with croutons and shaved Parmesan cheese.

title: Tortellini, Steak, and Caesar
description: Cheese tortellini, flank steak, and salad ingredients combine to yield a filling, delicious meal!

title: Caesar Salad Bites
description: Individual romaine lettuce leaves are topped with a little bit of Caesar dressing and Parmesan cheese creating Caesar salad bites perfect for parties.

title: Grilled Chicken Caesar Salad with Gouda
description: This grilled chicken Caesar salad with Gouda and bacon is the perfect lunch or dinner for a hot summer day.

title: Easy-Peasy Caesar Salad Lunch
description: Even picky eaters will jump for joy when they open their school lunch to find this easy Caesar salad with carrots and bacon.

title: Easy Rhubarb Crisp
description: In this rhubarb crisp recipe, tart rhubarb is layered between a buttery oat crust and oat crumble topping — a great way to use extra rhubarb in the spring.

title: Caldo Gallego (Galecian Broth)
description: Caldo gallego, a traditional Spanish soup full of turnips, turnip greens, white beans, ham, and sausage, makes a hearty and warm meal on a cold evening.

title: Alaska Salmon Bake with Pecan Crunch Coating
description: Baked salmon fillets with a crunchy pecan coating make an excellent main course.

title: Alaskan Cod and Shrimp with Fresh Tomato
description: This meal is very yummy, juicy, easy to cook, and convenient. It's ready in half an hour!

title: Halibut Cakes (Croquettes)
description: Flaked halibut is seasoned with onion, cheese, mayo, and lemon in these savory croquette cakes that make for a family-friendly main dish.

title: Creamy Halibut Olympia
description: Impress your guests with this recipe for classic baked Alaskan halibut Olympia in a creamy wine-caper sauce. Garnish with fresh dill weed and lemon.

title: Firecracker Grilled Alaska Salmon
description: A hot and sassy marinade makes this grilled salmon even more delicious.

title: Hearty Halibut Chowder
description: I got this recipe when I lived in Anchorage, Alaska. It's made from Alaskan halibut. The shredded carrots and Cheddar cheese in this chowder make it distinctive.

title: Salmon Fillets with Creamy Dill
description: A family recipe for how Alaskans make a delicious salmon dish, it combines mayonnaise and mustard with thyme, oregano, basil, and dill weed.

title: Slow Cooker Caribou Stew
description: Hearty caribou stew with plenty of vegetables and seasonings cooks all day in the slow cooker for a warm and comforting meal on cold evenings.

title: Slow Cooker Venison Sloppy Joes
description: Stew meat slow cooked with bacon and onion in a savory sauce of brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, ketchup and spices.

title: Grilled Salmon in Foil
description: Season salmon fillets and grill them in foil for a quick and easy meal that's great for entertaining or busy weeknights.

title: An Easy-as-Pie Sweet and Sour Sauce (no red sauce here...golden)
description: If you often find sweet and sour to be a little too 'sweet' and not enough 'sour,' try this recipe for a homemade version of the classic Asian sauce.

title: Pepper-Honey Cedar Plank Salmon
description: I live in Alaska and have 3 sons that love to fish. I have had to come up with some pretty creative ways to prepare salmon, this is by far my family and friends favorite way to eat fresh salmon. I soak an untreated cedar plank in water and bourbon while they are out fishing for the day and fix the barbeque sauce so that's it is ready to get grilling.....

title: Alaskan Sourdough Pancakes
description: Cooked on a griddle until golden brown, these sourdough pancakes are easy to make and will delight the whole family.

title: Wilderness Place Lodge Cookies
description: These cookies were created by the owners of Wilderness Place Lodge, in Lake Creek, Alaska. The owners are very good friends of mine, and the culinary creations at this fishing lodge are out of this world! I promise, one of these cookies will fill you as much as a cheeseburger and fries would!

title: Pan-Poached Alaskan Salmon Piccata
description: This elegant dish of salmon filets poached in lemon juice and chicken bouillon, then topped with butter and capers, is a great way to impress your significant other. Serve over cooked fettuccine or on its own with steamed vegetables and rice.

title: Salmonberry Cake
description: This simple cake is made with salmonberries, also known as cloudberries or bakeapples, native to the west coast of North America from Alaska to California.

title: Alaska Sheet Cake
description: Just like a Texas Sheet Cake, it uses the technique of boiling the water and butter, and it has a pecan frosting - but it's white instead of chocolate.

title: Lance's Balsamic Pickled Eggs
description: This pickled-egg recipe uses balsamic vinegar, fresh cayenne peppers, and the liquid from canned beets for a unique Alaskan delicacy.

title: Halibut Chowder with Cream Cheese
description: This huge pot of halibut chowder with bacon, cream cheese, and green onions is easy thanks to canned soup and makes enough to feed a crowd.

title: Alaskan Peanut Butter Ice Cream Pie
description: This recipe creates a simple peanut butter-flavored pie "crust" for filling with softened ice cream.

title: Alaskan Spicy Spinach Dip
description: Spicy, creamy, and colorful, this recipe is a splendid update to the Mexican spinach dip.

title: Strawberry Ice Cream
description: This strawberry ice cream recipe uses egg yolks and heavy cream to make a rich custard-style base for freshly pureed strawberries.

title: Lemon Rosemary Salmon
description: An easy yet impressive rosemary and lemon salmon, baked with bright, savory flavors. This dish works as a weeknight meal or special occasion dinner.

title: Chai Tea Latte
description: Make your own milky chai tea lattes with this homemade recipe that uses boiling water, milk, sugar, honey, and a chai tea bag. Delicious hot or iced!

title: Triple Berry Crisp
description: This berry crisp uses fresh raspberries, blackberries, and blueberries to make a juicy summer dessert with a buttery brown sugar and oat crumble.

title: Japanese-Style Sesame Green Beans
description: Fresh green beans get a flavor boost from sesame oil and a splash of soy sauce. Garnish with toasted sesame seeds.

title: Capers and Halibut
description: This is a very easy seared halibut with a buttery wine and caper sauce! It takes hardly any time at all to make, but it is sure to leave a lasting impression.

title: Classic Pear Crisp
description: Pears and crystallized ginger are baked under a crispy golden oat crust.

title: Sugar Snap Peas
description: Shallots and a little thyme are sprinkled over irresistible sugar snap peas!

title: Duck Confit, the Right Way
description: Rubbed in salt and bathed in duck fat, duck is slow-boiled, then crisped to make this savory confit that will be the star of dinner parties.

title: The Best Thai Curry-Peanut Sauce
description: This sweet and spicy peanut sauce is made with coconut milk, creamy peanut butter, and thai red curry paste.

title: Grilled Tri-Tip with Oregon Herb Rub
description: Tri-tip is a California central coast specialty, claimed to have been first introduced in the Santa Maria area. This recipe adds dill, sage, and rosemary to the basic Santa Maria recipe. The flavorful cut of meat really shines when it is grilled or smoked. Great with a green salad or layered onto French bread for a juicy beef sandwich.

title: Blackberry Cobbler
description: Try this simple blackberry cobbler recipe the next time you find yourself with an abundance of blackberries for a tasty, comforting dessert.

title: Blueberry Walnut Salad
description: An easy, yummy salad, perfect for any season, with berries, nuts, and greens. For an entree add chicken, diced apples, and diced green onions!

title: Grilled Halibut with Cilantro Garlic Butter
description: Delicious! My husband absolutely loves this recipe! Fish is simply seasoned with lime juice, then served with a cilantro lime garlic sauce. Serve over a bed of greens with a nice loaf of bread for a complete meal.

title: Shrimp and Crab Macaroni Salad
description: A chilled seafood macaroni salad with pasta, celery, onion, and green pepper. Imitation crabmeat also works well in place of real crab. Can also be made with salmon or tuna.

title: Chicken with Chanterelle Mushrooms and Marsala Wine
description: This take on a classic recipe combination of chicken and Marsala wine uses chanterelle mushrooms and plenty of butter to deliver a tasty chicken main dish.

title: Raspberry Almond Coffee Cake
description: This moist, light cake is "berry" delicious as a dessert or for breakfast. Your house will smell just wonderful while it is baking and cooling. Recipe doubles well.

title: Oregon Salmon Patties
description: This excellent recipe for salmon patties comes from the Oregon coast. You can use canned or fresh salmon to make these easy salmon cakes to enjoy.

title: Rainy Portland (Warm Rum Drink)
description: Warm yourself up with this 'Rainy Portland' drink made with warmed milk, brown sugar, rum, and a hint of butter.

title: Sugar Snap Peas with Mint
description: Simple and quick to prepare. Sugar snap peas are quickly fried with green onion and garlic, and tossed with fresh mint leaves. Wonderful use for spring garden vegetables. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: Shrimp and Sugar Snap Peas
description: Quick and easy pasta dish with a little bite that will make anyone look like a gourmet chef. Adjust the chili oil to your own spice level.

title: Danish Peppernut Christmas Cookies (Pebernodder)
description: Spicy cookies are a beloved Christmas treat in Denmark and throughout Scandinavia where expensive spices were traditionally reserved for special holiday foods. These tiny (nut-free) butter cookies burst with flavor from cardamom, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves.

title: Fresh Pear Bread
description: This moist, delicious bread is made with fresh pears and flavored with vanilla pudding mix and cinnamon.

title: Highway Cafe Chess Pie
description: I obtained this recipe 40-years ago from the cook at the Highway Cafe in Scappoose, Oregon. I have never found its equal. Whenever I serve it, I am always asked for the recipe.

title: Strawberries in Spiced Syrup
description: This is a great recipe using ingredients already stocked in your cabinet and one my husband said was knock you to your knees delicious. Serve with fresh whipped cream and enjoy.

title: Spicy Fruit Salsa
description: A sweet and spicy fresh fruit salsa starring kiwi, strawberries, blackberries, and apples; seasoned with cayenne, hot sauce, green salsa, and lime juice. Serve with tortilla chips

title: Tangy Pear and Blue Cheese Salad
description: Romaine, blue cheese, chopped pears, walnuts, and red onion, combined with a tangy dressing, make this salad unforgettable. It is a sure hit worth trying!

title: Magical Unicorn Poop Meringues
description: A fun project for kids, these rainbow-colored unicorn poop meringues sparkle with edible glitter and are ideal for easy entertaining.

title: Sugared Black Raspberry Tea Cookies
description: Petite, crunchy, black raspberry filled thumbprints, dipped in granulated sugar, and studded with miniature chocolate chips. These cookies freeze well.

title: Artichoke Crab Dip
description: This hot dip is simple and wonderful! Lump crabmeat is folded into a creamy artichoke mixture. Serve with crackers or warm bread slices.

title: Berry Refresher
description: This recipe is a perfect refresher for a hot summer day or to quench a raging thirst! Absolutely delicious! To make it thick, simply use berries frozen!

title: Strawberry Soup III
description: Strawberries are blended with buttermilk in this chilled soup sweetened to taste with white sugar.

title: Idaho Fry Sauce
description: This mayonnaise-based fry sauce with tangy seasoning is just what you need to jazz up your french fries. Made with easy ingredients you already have.

title: Grilled Salmon
description: A simple soy sauce and brown sugar marinade, with hints of lemon and garlic, are the perfect salty-sweet complement to rich salmon fillets.

title: Cedar Planked Salmon
description: Cedar-plank salmon is tops for flavor. This streamlined recipe uses a quick soy, scallion, and ginger marinade that's speedy enough for weeknights.

title: Chinese Pork Dumplings
description: These fried Chinese dumplings are from Liana Cafe House in Seattle's International District. You can make them at home with this authentic recipe!

title: Fresh Cherry Cobbler
description: This delicious cherry cobbler is made with fresh cherries rather than canned. Pitting the cherries will be well worth it when you taste this treat.

title: Texas Sausage Kolaches (Klobasneks)
description: In Central Texas, sausage kolaches (also called klobasneks) are plentiful and sold in every bakery. If you're craving the real thing, try this recipe!

title: Beets on the Grill
description: Easy roasted beets in foil that get cooked on the grill. A great way to prepare flavorful beets without any mess. They don't even need to be peeled.

title: Surprise Banulla Cake
description: This easy banulla cake with walnuts is a simple, one-bowl recipe for a moist and tender dessert full of flavor from lots of mashed, overripe banullas.

title: Panko-Breaded Fried Razor Clams
description: Pan-fried razor clams in a crunchy crust make a tasty shellfish appetizer when breaded with coarse Japanese panko bread crumbs. Allow enough additional time before cooking to freeze breaded clams so the coating sticks well.

title: Baked Asparagus with Balsamic Butter Sauce
description: Asparagus with balsamic butter sauce is a simple and delicious side dish. Bake them until tender, then pour a buttery soy and balsamic mixture over top.

title: Easy Swedish Apple Pie
description: This lovely Swedish apple pie covered with a sweet, cinnamon crust is perfectly tart and tasty. It's easy to make too, no need to roll out dough.

title: Best Ever Caramel Apple Crisp
description: "When our class visited an apple farm this fall, we realized that we all shared a common love apples dipped in caramel. We created this really easy dessert that the whole family can enjoy."

title: Mushroom Risotto
description: Delicious mushroom risotto made with vegetable broth, cream, and a variety of fresh vegetables. Serve as a side dish or filling main course.

title: Seattle Cream Cheese Dogs
description: On the streets of Seattle, after the bars close, and during sporting events, these are a local favorite--warm cream cheese spread on your favorite hotdog!

title: Good-for-You Greek Salad
description: This tomato and cucumber salad with feta is light but has big taste packed into every bite, thanks to briny olives and a fresh sprinkling of lemon juice.

title: Sesame Noodle Salad
description: Served chilled or warm, this noodle salad easily pairs with your favorite summertime foods.

title: New Red Potato Salad
description: This simple chilled potato salad makes great use of unpeeled red potatoes, hard cooked eggs, celery and a mayonnaise mixture. It's perfect for the big cookout!

title: Barbeque Halibut Steaks
description: A simple recipe for barbecued halibut. Soy sauce and brown sugar add a special zip that is uncommonly delicious.

title: Salmon with Brown Sugar and Bourbon Glaze
description: Salmon is cooked in a glaze of butter, brown sugar and bourbon.

title: Anne's Fabulous Grilled Salmon
description: This is a grilled salmon recipe that is used at the Saint Matthew Parish picnic every year in Seattle, Washington. It works well with any cut of salmon for grilling, however we typically use salmon fillets. Use wild sockeye or king salmon.

title: Zesty Marinated Asparagus
description: Tender asparagus is marinated in a balsamic vinaigrette and sprinkled with tangy lemon zest and fresh parsley. This is a quick and easy side dish.

title: Twenty-Four Hour Salad
description: A layered green salad with green peas, celery, bell peppers, Cheddar cheese, and bacon sprinkled over all. For other variations, I have substituted or added some of my own favorite ingredients, such as: carrots, eggs, mushrooms, sprouts, and seeded cucumbers.

title: Dried Apricot Jam
description: Dried apricots with a hint of vanilla can be re-hydrated and made into jam any time of the year. Apricot jam makes a colorful and sweet gift everyone will enjoy.

title: Salmon with Dill
description: Baked salmon with onion powder and dried dill weed. With just a hint of seasoning, you can make salmon taste delicious.

title: Baked Fresh Cherry Pie
description: If you've never eaten a fresh cherry pie, you're in for a treat. It's a bit of work to pit the cherries, but once this is done, there's not much left to do to make the filling: just mix the cherries with almond and vanilla extracts, sugar, tapioca, and a pinch of salt.

title: Fried Morel Mushrooms
description: Morel mushrooms are a treat of nature, they are only available from the wild and they are prized for their honeycomb texture and rich, earthy flavor. In this recipe morels are lightly breaded and fried to golden perfection They are best prepared simply in recipes that really show them off, and this is a great one!

title: New England Razor Clam Chowder
description: Bacon, potatoes, and clams in a creamy chowder make a hearty and delicious meal.

title: Jalapeno Poppers of Champions
description: Jalapeno pepper halves are filled with cream cheese, wrapped with meatless bacon strips and baked to delicious football-lovin' perfection!

title: Submarine Flavors
description: Flavored oil for Italian submarine sandwiches.

title: Applesauce Raisin Cake
description: A simple, moist and delicious cake made with raisins, walnuts and applesauce.

title: Fried Razor Clams
description: A simple recipe for fried razor clams, a western Washington treat. Coat with crushed crackers and dip in cocktail sauce. The spicier the better!

title: Ginger Salmon
description: The wonderful natural flavor of salmon is greatly enhanced by the addition of a tangy glaze made with ginger, honey, and Dijon mustard.

title: Warm Apple Pocket
description: Like an apple pie sandwich! - Sliced apples and spices folded into prepared pie crust. So easy it makes you just want to put it in your pocket!

title: Dijon Crusted Halibut
description: Delightful baked halibut breaded with a spicy mixture of Dijon mustard, horseradish, fresh Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.

title: Chicken Enchiladas with Mole Sauce
description: These authentic chicken enchiladas are topped with a rich and flavorful mole sauce made with chocolate and dried chiles. Delicious!

title: Chanterelle Risotto
description: Savory and cheesy chanterelle risotto. This is a sublime vegetarian dish for dinner parties. You can substitute Romano for Parmesan cheese and porcinis for chanterelles.

title: Wazzu Tailgate Chili
description: This simple cornmeal chili is full of flavor and plenty spicy. It's best made a day ahead, refrigerated overnight, then reheated right before the big game.

title: Sweet Onion Pie
description: This delicious onion pie has a buttery cracker crumb crust and is stuffed with sweet onions, garlic, chives, and Cheddar cheese.

title: Joe's Special Scramble
description: This Joe's special recipe makes a beefy scramble with spinach, eggs, and mushrooms that can be enjoyed at any meal. It's a Seattle favorite!

title: Mimi's Smoked Salmon Chowder
description: Smoked salmon stars with potatoes, celery, onion, herbs, and spices in this hearty chicken stock-based chowder that's pure Pacific Northwest comfort food.

title: Lemon Garlic Salmon
description: Salmon fillets seasoned with lemon pepper are pan-fried in garlic butter for a quick and delicious weeknight meal that takes just 30 minutes to make.

title: Garlic Asparagus with Lime
description: A splash of lime lends zesty freshness to this early spring favorite.

title: Fresh Fruit Cobbler
description: Slices of sugared fresh fruit - peaches, pears, plums, and cherries - are piled into a large casserole dish and covered with a sweet batter. Thirty minutes later, the cobbler emerges bubbling, fragrant, and golden brown.

title: Savory French Crepes
description: At 611 Supreme in Seattle, authentic Normandy-style buckwheat crepes are filled with either savory or sweet fillings. Let the batter rest overnight before making the crepes.

title: Makhani Chicken (Indian Butter Chicken)
description: This fragrant, spicy Indian butter chicken recipe with yogurt marinade is from the owner of India Cuisine restaurant in Seattle, Washington. Serve with hot Indian bread.

title: Early American Eggnog
description: This traditional version of classic eggnog is suspected of having roots dating to George Washington's era, but it certainly pulls out all the stops. A creamy blend of egg yolks, egg whites, heavy cream, milk, rum, brandy, and sherry, it requires aging at least 5 to 10 days to achieve its remarkable mellow taste.

title: Garlic Salmon
description: A large salmon fillet, steamed in foil and cooked either in the oven or barbecue. It's seasoned with minced garlic, fresh baby dill, lemon slices, fresh ground pepper, and green onions.

title: Scott's Coast-to-Coast Famous Chicken Wings
description: Deep-fried chicken wings coated in a buttery hot sauce is a Buffalo original that is now a national sensation. Follow this recipe for perfect wings.

title: Corn, Sweet Onion, and Tomato Salad
description: An exciting, cool and refreshing side salad that goes great with grilled meat. Fantastic for get-togethers. It's also really quick and easy to prepare...no cooking needed!

title: Seattle Dutch Babies
description: A rich popover pancake served with melted butter, powder sugar, lemon wedges or fresh fruit. A dish that's well known in Seattle, Washington.

title: Fair Scones
description: Freshly baked scones just like at the fairgrounds are ready to eat in less than an hour. Serve with butter and raspberry jam.

title: Mashed Potato Salad
description: These are so good, you'll want to run out in the middle of the night and buy up all the red and Yukon gold potatoes at the market. This dynamic duo and the mayonnaise/mustard/sour cream dressing, make all the difference. Serves six.

title: Goat Cheese Arugula Pizza - No Red Sauce!
description: This pesto-based pizza is an amazingly simple and delicious variation to your regular pizza. Adapted from a pizza idea at a popular Neapolitan pizza restaurant in Washington DC, it'll take minutes to make and will disappear in even less time!

title: Sweet Washington Cherry Pie
description: Make this richly flavored sweet cherry pie when the fresh cherries from eastern Washington are in season.

title: Emily's Famous Tiramisu
description: Homemade ladyfingers are soaked in a rum-coffee syrup and layered with sweetened mascarpone in this elegant tiramisu made in a springform pan.

title: Erika's "Frango" Mints
description: Passed on through the generations, this recipe for the famous Frango® mints makes a perfect holiday or hostess gift.

title: Blueberry Cherry Pie
description: Who would have thought? Blueberries and cherries in the same pie. But they 're divine together. You 'll have to pit the cherries, but it should be a labor of love. The berries are sugared, dusted with flour and cinnamon, and dotted with butter. The oven takes care of the rest.

description: Zucchini, corn, and onions are cooked in a skillet and topped with crispy crumbled bacon and shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

description: Milk, cocoa powder, butter, and sugar are simmered together in this Southern-style chocolate gravy; serve over buttermilk biscuits.

title: Dylan's Potato, Carrot, and Cheddar Soup
description: Potatoes, carrots, and Cheddar cheese combine with chicken broth to make this simple and tasty soup.

title: Chanterelle Mushroom and Bacon Tartlets
description: Wild chanterelle mushrooms and bacon combine wonderfully in this impressive and elegant starter.

title: Valentine Pizza
description: Make this pizza for your Valentine! The rosemary dough is made in a bread machine, and then made into three heart shaped pizzas.

title: Grace Love's Smothered Steak
description: Chuck steak is seasoned with a special spice rub and baked with vegetables until fork-tender in this comforting Smothered Steak recipe.

title: Old Fashioned Apple Cream Pie
description: Tart, sweetened apples, with a bit of lemon juice and butter stirred in, are cooked on the stove until tender. Then they 're spooned over a wonderful cream cheese and vanilla pudding filling, and brushed with an apricot glaze.

description: A simple soy sauce and brown sugar marinade, with hints of lemon and garlic, are the perfect salty-sweet complement to rich salmon fillets.

description: Salmon fillets seasoned with lemon pepper are pan-fried in garlic butter for a quick and delicious weeknight meal that takes just 30 minutes to make.

title: Savory French Crepes
description: At 611 Supreme in Seattle, authentic Normandy-style buckwheat crepes are filled with either savory or sweet fillings. Let the batter rest overnight before making the crepes.

title: Makhani Chicken (Indian Butter Chicken)
description: This fragrant, spicy Indian butter chicken recipe with yogurt marinade is from the owner of India Cuisine restaurant in Seattle, Washington. Serve with hot Indian bread.

title: Garlic Salmon
description: A large salmon fillet, steamed in foil and cooked either in the oven or barbecue. It's seasoned with minced garlic, fresh baby dill, lemon slices, fresh ground pepper, and green onions.

title: Scott's Coast-to-Coast Famous Chicken Wings
description: Deep-fried chicken wings coated in a buttery hot sauce is a Buffalo original that is now a national sensation. Follow this recipe for perfect wings.

title: Seattle Dutch Babies
description: A rich popover pancake served with melted butter, powder sugar, lemon wedges or fresh fruit. A dish that's well known in Seattle, Washington.

title: Emily's Famous Tiramisu
description: Homemade ladyfingers are soaked in a rum-coffee syrup and layered with sweetened mascarpone in this elegant tiramisu made in a springform pan.

title: Erika's "Frango" Mints
description: Passed on through the generations, this recipe for the famous Frango® mints makes a perfect holiday or hostess gift.

title: Corn and Zucchini Melody
description: Zucchini, corn, and onions are cooked in a skillet and topped with crispy crumbled bacon and shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

title: Art's Southern-Style Chocolate Gravy
description: Milk, cocoa powder, butter, and sugar are simmered together in this Southern-style chocolate gravy; serve over buttermilk biscuits.

title: Dylan's Potato, Carrot, and Cheddar Soup
description: Potatoes, carrots, and Cheddar cheese combine with chicken broth to make this simple and tasty soup.

title: Valentine Pizza
description: Make this pizza for your Valentine! The rosemary dough is made in a bread machine, and then made into three heart shaped pizzas.

title: Grace Love's Smothered Steak
description: Chuck steak is seasoned with a special spice rub and baked with vegetables until fork-tender in this comforting Smothered Steak recipe.

title: Seahawk Burger
description: Build a burger worthy of the NFC Champion Seattle Seahawks using a grass-fed beef burger, Washington state cheese, wine, arugula, and a Sriracha and espresso infused aioli.

title: Seattle Smoked Salmon Dip
description: Smoked salmon takes center stage folded into mayo, lemon juice and McCormick® Guacamole Seasoning Mix. Serve with crackers, crusty bread, sliced apple or pita chips.

title: Beast Mode Vodka
description: This brightly-colored vodka drink was fashioned to celebrate the Seattle Seahawks, their team colors, and their awe-inspiring running back.

title: Blueberry Pie Pops
description: Delectable little 2-bite blueberry pielets on sticks will bring out the kid in you. Tuck one or two in a lunchbox, or sit a bunch up in a vase for people to take with their coffee. Cute and tasty wins the day!

title: Seattle Caramel Apples
description: Trail mix adds a nutty texture to these delicious caramel apples.

title: Seattle's Favorite Kale Salad
description: Kale salad with warm wild rice and cabbage is tossed in a tangy lemon dressing and tastes just like the kale salad from Seattle's PCC Natural Market.

title: Aglio e Olio alla Fremont
description: Aglio e olio, a traditional Italian dish of spaghetti tossed with garlic and olive oil, gets a hearty addition of hazelnuts in this recipe for a delightful meal similar to an Italian restaurant in Seattle.

title: Seattle Salmon Burgers
description: A cream cheese and onion twist makes these Seattle salmon burgers a delicious way to enjoy fresh or leftover salmon fillets on brioche buns.

title: Li'l Woody's Farmers Market Burger
description: Seasoned beef patties are topped with goat cheese, heirloom tomatoes, and arugula in these farmers market burgers bursting with meaty flavor.

title: Big-Batch Roquefort Dressing
description: This version of a blue cheese salad dressing, said to hail from a Seattle restaurant, calls for Roquefort in a creamy buttermilk, sour cream, and mayonnaise base.

title: Roast Leg of Lamb with Rosemary
description: A leg of lamb is marinated overnight with rosemary, garlic, mustard, honey, and lemon zest, then roasted to perfection for a family-pleasing meal.

title: Red Garlic Mashed Potatoes
description: These garlic mashed red potatoes make the creamiest, most delicious side. Quick and easy to make, they are always a favorite to serve with any meal.

title: Roasted Garlic Mashed Potatoes
description: Roasted garlic mashed potatoes are creamy, full of flavor, and easy to make. Serve them alongside any meat or fish, or layer them over a casserole.

title: Not Your Everyday Smoked Pork Spareribs
description: These family-favorite smoked spareribs are slightly sweet and spicy with an apple cider-based mop sauce that complements the fall-off-the-bone meat.

title: Foil Barbecued Trout with Wine
description: Trout is sealed in aluminum foil with a delicious blend of ingredients, then quickly grilled to serve for dinner. A quick, easy and delicious way to cook trout.

title: Grilled London Broil
description: Lemon pepper, lemon juice, and tarragon vinegar add sparkle to tenderized and marinated London broil steak. The recipe can be multiplied to do enough meat for a party.

title: Raspberry Jalapeno Jelly
description: Homemade raspberry jam--made with fresh or frozen raspberries--is livened up with spicy jalapeno peppers.

title: Asian Rainbow Trout
description: Flavors of Asia come together in this delicious, simple recipe that I put together after asking various people what to do with rainbow trout!

title: Pork Sausage Gravy
description: Hearty pork sausage and gravy to pour over homemade biscuits or toast. Water may be substituted for the milk.

title: Hunter's Venison Casserole
description: This delicious layered casserole of mashed potatoes, venison, vegetables, and cottage cheese provides a hearty and warming, all-in-one meal.

title: Easy Roast Leg of Lamb
description: A boneless leg of lamb is seasoned with slivers of garlic and fresh rosemary, then roasted with tomato sauce for a mouth-watering holiday main dish.

title: Summer Sausage
description: This garlicky summer sausage is easy to make in your oven! Add or omit spices as desired, then add the finished sausages to holiday gift baskets!

title: Beef or Moose Jerky
description: This beef or moose jerky recipe is smokey, savory, and sweet. Marinate rump roast for rich flavor, then it's done in just 12 hours in a dehydrator.

title: Mesquite Smoked Jerky
description: This beef jerky tastes just like the store-bought kind. If you like those kinds, you'll enjoy this very much. You can use hickory-smoked flavoring instead, if desired.

title: Spicy Beefstick
description: A spicy beefstick snack recipe made with ground beef, pork sausage, mustard seed, liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, and an array of spices.

title: White Chili
description: This ground turkey chili is made with great Northern beans, salsa, corn, and pepper-jack cheese. It is very tasty and a little spicy; if you don't like it spicy, cut the amount of cheese in half--it will still have a little kick!

title: Rainbow Trout with Yogurt Sauce
description: Tender and mild trout with a tangy yogurt sauce. Serve with crusty bread and lemon potatoes. If you can, use freshly caught trout.

title: Bratwurst, Sauerkraut and Bean Casserole
description: Wanted to do something different with brats, so I put this together from ingredients I had in the cupboard.

title: Steve's Bodacious Barbecue Ribs
description: These make real mouth-watering 'Pig-cicles'! They take a while to cook, and when you eat them, you'll have pork fat smeared from ear to ear! Mmm! Mmm! I like to smoke with hickory wood, but any of your favorite will suffice.

title: Beefy Cabbage Stew
description: Ground beef is simmered with pinto beans, kidney beans, diced tomatoes, corn, tomato juice and coleslaw mix for this easy dinner. Serve with cornbread, if desired.

title: White Bean, Spinach, and Barley Stew
description: This filling vegetarian stew is great year-round. Serve with a dry Chardonnay and crusty bread.

title: Bill's Smoked BBQ Baby Back Ribs
description: Apple juice and garlic add flavor to these fall-off-the-bone ribs that are smoked for 7 hours.

title: Venison Kabobs with Sweet and Smoky Sauce
description: Venison marinates in an Asian-spiced tomato sauce in this delicious, gamey take on an old BBQ favorite.

title: Wyoming Stew
description: Wonderful stew recipe with crescent rolls laid on top in a pie formation. I used this recipe when I used to work up in Cody, Wyoming. If you do not own a cast-iron skillet, use a 9-inch casserole dish instead, and cook the filling in a saucepan. Makes a lovely presentation.

title: Cookson Stew
description: Six bean stew with pork sausage and BBQ sauce.

title: Fresh Southern Peach Cobbler
description: This peach cobbler recipe makes the perfect dessert. Sweet Georgia peaches are topped with homemade biscuits creating a bubbling Southern-style peach cobbler perfect for summer nights.

title: Dave's Low Country Boil
description: Low country boil is a famously flavorful one-pot feast of seafood, sausage, potatoes, and corn. It's an outdoor cooking classic, but fun indoors too.

title: Georgia Peach Homemade Ice Cream
description: This peach ice cream recipe is an easy-to-make, no-cook, eggless summertime frozen treat made with fresh peaches, sugar, cream, and 3 types of milk.

title: Old-Fashioned Roasted Pecans
description: These roasted pecans are baked in the oven with brown sugar, cinnamon, and a bit of salt for a sweet, Southern-style snack at Christmas or year-round.

title: Southern Style Dry Rub for Pork or Chicken
description: This pork or chicken dry rub recipe is a favorite in Southern Georgia; use it to season ribs, pork roast, or chicken for a delicious boost of flavor.

title: Khachapuri (Georgian Cheese Bread)
description: This ajarski khachapuri recipe is Chef John's version of boat-shaped, leavened Georgian bread filled with 3 cheeses, butter, and warm, runny egg yolk.

title: The Right Way to Cook Greens!
description: Learn how to cook greens using bacon drippings, salt, and a cast iron skillet to sauté collards briefly or simmer with water for extra tenderness.

title: Georgia Cornbread Cake
description: This Georgia cornbread cake is more like a brown sugar and pecan cake. It's actually made without cornmeal and tastes similar to blonde brownies.

title: Dave's Georgia Black-Eyed Peas
description: This tasty black-eyed peas recipe involves cooking the black-eyed peas low and slow with bacon, onion, and ham. Serve with cornbread for a hearty meal.

title: Savannah's Best Marinated Portobello Mushrooms
description: Marinate portobello mushroom caps for 15 minutes with a mixture of garlic, balsamic vinegar, and soy so they'll be just the right texture after cooking.

title: Vidalia Sweet Onion Dip
description: Thinly-sliced Vidalia sweet onion is baked in a mixture of mayonnaise, Swiss cheese, and Parmesan cheese for this creamy dip.

title: GA Peach Pound Cake
description: This Georgia peach pound cake can also be made with other fruits such as apple or cherry.

title: Deep-Fried Peanuts
description: Deep-fried peanuts are a Southern delicacy and an excellent crowd-pleasing snack or appetizer.

title: Traditional Brunswick Stew
description: This simple, hearty stew consists of chicken and salt pork with potatoes, beans and other vegetables seasoned with Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.

title: Peach Cobbler VI
description: This is a wonderful Southern recipe... very easy and tastes great!

title: Grandpa's Tomato Gravy
description: A simple Southern tomato gravy that can be served over rice, pasta, biscuits, or grits.

title: Fourteen Layer Chocolate Cake
description: Fourteen very thin layers with chocolate between each layer. Hope you enjoy this! I am from Georgia and make it all the time for church functions and family reunions.

title: Georgia Cracker Salad
description: Crackers are tossed with tomato, egg and green onion in the quick mayonnaise salad. This is a traditional Southern salad. Best if eaten immediately upon preparing.

title: Lime Fluff
description: A Georgia favorite! Great with everything! Make a lot for large gatherings, it disappears quickly! You can use any kind of nuts you like; adjust the amount to suit your preference.

title: Georgia Spiced Peaches
description: This is an old, old recipe from relatives in Georgia.

title: Lemony Caesar Salad Dressing
description: Fresh lemon juice and extra light olive oil give a fresh taste to the classic creamy salad dressing. Serve over torn romaine lettuce leaves with a sprinkling of croutons.

title: Georgia Sunset
description: Brandy and peach schnapps make a beautiful and deliciously fruity Georgia sunset cocktail.

title: Ratatouille Bake
description: Garden veggies, including eggplant and zucchini, are layered onto ready-made cheese ravioli, topped with mozzarella cheese, and baked.

title: Georgia's Tennessee Jam Cake
description: This rich holiday dessert was invented by my grandmother and is a tradition in our house over Christmas. These ingredients were originally the authentic thing -- homemade jam, buttermilk out of the churn, and walnuts you gather and crack yourself. Now we use purchased items, but the cake is just as good. Frost with homemade caramel frosting, or your favorite cream cheese frosting.

title: Prune Cake
description: This rich spice cake is made with buttermilk, cooked dried plums, and chopped pecans, then topped with a sweet buttermilk icing.

title: South Georgia Biscuits
description: These are traditional hand-formed South Georgia biscuits as made by my family for generations. Unlike most recipes, these biscuits are formed entirely by hand, not rolled and cut. Once you master the technique, you can make them very quickly and will find the texture and appearance to be much better than rolled biscuits.

title: Simple Mint Julep
description: Mint, bourbon, and sugar are mixed with ice in this classic mint julep recipe that is quick and easy to prepare for the Kentucky derby.

title: Oyster Stew Christmas Eve Recipe
description: A little Louisiana-style hot sauce gives this oyster stew a bit of a kick, while the green onion and red bell pepper add color.

title: Georgia Caviar
description: Black-eyed peas in a zesty marinade make a wonderful dip for tortilla chips or bread. Serve at room temperature.

title: Khachapuri
description: Khachapuri is a homemade bread stuffed with Muenster cheese, an Eastern European treat from Georgia great for breakfast or as a party snack.

title: Georgia Peach Pie
description: My mom's summer dessert! So easy and fast to make. A vanilla meringue base with pecans is topped with sliced peaches and whipped cream. Make it early in the day; the longer the peaches sit on the crust the better!!!

title: Vidalia Onion Soup
description: A huge hit for dinner, the sweet taste of Vidalia onions combines with chicken broth and cream for a rich, deeply flavored treat. The soup is blended in a blender, so it comes out so creamy and thick! If you like Vidalias, you'll love this soup. You can make a lighter version by using milk and no heavy cream.

title: Nasty Cake
description: Make a packaged devil's food cake, poke some holes in it, and smother the hot cake with a decadent, buttery syrup for a delicious, Southern treat.

title: Georgia Country Ham and Redeye Gravy
description: Redeye gravy is simply butter and ham drippings deglazed with breakfast coffee; serve with country ham for this authentic Georgian recipe.

title: Georgia Shake
description: A chocolate peanut butter cup is blended with chocolate ice cream and milk.

title: Harmon's Brunswick Stew
description: Brunswick stew doesn't get much easier than this recipe calling for cans of prepared beef bbq, pork bbq, crushed tomatoes, cream-style corn, and chicken.

title: Laurel's Lasagna
description: A hearty blend of ground beef and pork is sauteed with onions and simmered with mushrooms, tomatoes, garlic, sugar and a medley of spices. Layered with noodles and cheeses, this earthy casserole is a crowd pleaser.

title: Georgia Nuggets
description: A light browns sugar candy similar to Divinity is studded with pecans. This is a candy recipe that I share with all my family and friends at Christmas.

title: Peaches 'n Cream Shortcake
description: Fresh peaches and whipped cream combine in this delicious peaches and cream shortcake, the perfect summer dessert when peaches are in season.

title: Slow Cooker Creamed Corn
description: The best creamed corn with cream cheese — simmered with butter and milk in the slow cooker for a rich and delicious side that everyone will love.

title: Grandma Oma's Pickled Okra
description: Pickled okra flavored with dried red chile peppers and dill; great for gift-giving! These pickles make a refreshing change on a relish tray.

title: Simple Grilled Lamb Chops
description: These grilled lamb chops are tender, juicy, and full of flavor thanks to a garlic marinade. An easy-to-prep recipe for an impressive summer meal!

title: Southern Grits Casserole
description: This grits casserole made with sausage, grits, and Cheddar cheese is ready in an hour and can be kept warm in a slow cooker at your breakfast buffet.

title: Simple Country Ribs
description: Ribs are boiled in barbeque sauce before grilling over high heat to produce extra tasty, deliciously moist, fall-off-the-bone pork ribs.

title: Slow Roasted BBQ Beef Roast
description: BBQ roast beef goes round and round on an outdoor rotisserie grill, coated in a mouthwatering blend of dried spices. Juicy, tender, and full of flavor!

title: Best Ever Pinto Beans
description: This hearty pinto bean dish uses smoked ham hock to add flavor and richness. A bit of tomato sauce and brown sugar gives this meal a little zing.

title: Beer and Brown Sugar Steak Marinade
description: I concocted this marinade on a lark and it turned out great. The flavors complement and do not overwhelm the natural taste of beef.

title: Easy Barbeque Beef Tenderloin Steak
description: For sensational flavor, rub nice thick tenderloin steaks with olive oil, crushed garlic and meat tenderizer. Let the meat sit for a bit and then grill.

title: Cream of Asparagus and Mushroom Soup
description: The savory flavors of mushrooms and bacon make this cream of asparagus soup a warm starter course for a meal.

title: New Year's Day Black-Eyed Peas
description: See in the new year with a hearty bowl of black-eyed peas cooked with garlic, onion, tomatoes and diced country ham. A real country ham is quite salty, but the flavor and seasoning is just right for this homey dish.

title: Black-eyed Peas and Ham Hocks
description: Black-eyed peas simmered with ham hocks and seasoning for a true Southern craving!

title: Oklahoma Brisket
description: This is absolutely fabulous and so easy. Brisket that isn't dried out can be so good. The bar-b-que sauce is also wonderful and can be used for other meat dishes.

title: Okra Patties
description: These fried okra patties are made from fresh okra and onion in a cornmeal batter. A delightful southern-style snack.

title: Country Sausage Gravy
description: Thick and creamy pork sausage gravy with fresh sage, thyme and red pepper flakes for a little kick.

title: Winter Blossom's Often Requested Ham Salad
description: A fast, simple chopped ham salad that is great for parties, lunches, or even on toast for breakfast.

title: Oklahoma Indian Tacos
description: Easy-to-make Indian tacos made with fry bread that uses just two ingredients: self-rising flour and buttermilk. Top the golden brown fried bread with spicy ground beef and bean mixture, then garnish with your favorite taco trimmings.

title: Best Bourbon Chicken
description: Chunks of chicken breast are simmered in a fruity, zesty sauce made with sippin' whiskey liqueur for a Southern treat.

title: Grilled Buffalo Wings
description: This is a great recipe for grilled chicken wings. They are much better than fried!

title: Spicy Bean Salsa
description: This spicy bean dip is a nice variation of traditional tomato salsa, enlivened with black beans, corn, and black-eyed peas.

title: Easy Grilled Tri-Tip
description: Slices of beef tri tip are marinated and grilled. This is a great easy summer barbeque idea!

title: Chicken Fried Steak
description: Breaded beef cutlets are dipped in buttermilk and egg batter, then fried and served with pan gravy in this family recipe used for years.

title: Oklahoma Cheese Grits
description: It's a great day when my mom serves up this Southern specialty! Cooked grits are combined with seasonings, cheese, and eggs, then baked. You may adjust or eliminate the hot sauce to suit your taste.

title: Honey Crunch Pecan Pie
description: This pecan pie filling is made with a honey custard, flavored with vanilla and bourbon.

title: Brown Bean Chowder
description: This bean chowder is similar to chili. It's one of the most popular dishes at Tulsa Public Schools. Those of us growing up in the 60's and 70's remember it fondly as a favorite treat. A real stick-to-your-ribs comfort food. Tradition dictates that it is served with cinnamon rolls. This was given to me by my grandmother who was a dietician/cook for over 40 years.

title: Depression Era Corn Chowder
description: This corn chowder is made with just corn, potatoes, chicken broth, evaporated milk, onion and butter.

title: Southern Pecan Pie II
description: A homemade crust made with butter and egg yolk encases this classic Southern style pecan pie.

title: Soft Cheese Tacos
description: Soft cheese tacos include corn tortillas rolled around Cheddar cheese that are topped with a cheese sauce for a Mexican-inspired comfort food.

title: Corn Cornbread
description: This is a rich loaf with sour cream and canned corn for extra flavor. Try adding chopped peppers or onions for variations on the theme.

title: High-Altitude Buttermilk Devil's Food Cake
description: Buttermilk makes this devil's food cake moist and tender, perfect for bakers at high altitudes looking to make a celebratory 3-layer cake.

title: Oklahoma Tamale Casserole
description: Canned beef tamales and cooked chicken are combined in this easy, hearty, Southwestern themed casserole.

title: Gloria's Sausage Gravy with Biscuits
description: This is a wonderful sausage gravy and biscuit recipe my cousin serves for breakfast on special occasions.

title: Instant Pot® Coconut-Caramel Shrimp
description: This Americanized version of Vietnamese coconut-caramel shrimp is made in the Instant Pot® and is excellent when served with jasmine rice cooked in coconut milk.

title: Sarah's Stewed Taco Burgers
description: These south of the border beef burgers are stewed in a taco seasoned tomato and onion sauce, resulting in a super-moist burger.

title: Southwest Chicken
description: Healthy and hearty, chicken simmers with tomatoes, black beans and corn.

title: Biscochitos Traditional Cookies
description: Biscochitos are a classic Christmas cookie in New Mexico. These delicious anise-flavored shortbread-like cookies are dusted with sugar and cinnamon.

title: New Mexico Green Chile Stew
description: Green chiles, beef, and pork cubes simmer in the slow cooker with potatoes, tomatoes, herbs, and spices for a deliciously fragrant stew. It is great to serve with tortillas, tortilla chips, green onions, and sour cream.

title: Santa Fe Stew
description: This ground beef stew is easy to make thanks to use of canned beans and vegetables, making it a great winter dinner for busy parents.

title: New Mexico Red Chile Sauce
description: Red chile sauce is a favorite in New Mexican and West Texan cuisine; this recipe includes aromatic toasted red pepper pods and chicken stock

title: Santa Fe Hatch Chile Green Sauce
description: Santa Fe Hatch chiles are roasted and chopped into a versatile green sauce flavored with garlic and beef broth and thickened with flour.

title: Easy Slow Cooker Santa Fe Chicken
description: Get a taste of the American southwest from your slow cooker with this recipe featuring chicken, diced tomatoes with green chiles, corn, and cilantro.

title: New Mexico Green Chile Breakfast Burritos
description: A hearty recipe for a style of breakfast burrito found in every eatery, taco stand, and gas station around Santa Fe, made with the famous green chiles from Hatch, New Mexico.

title: Authentic Mexican Hot Sauce
description: Combining a variety of toasted, dried chile pods with vinegar and garlic, this is the sort of hot sauce you might find on the neighborhood taco wagon. It is a little time consuming but well worth it.

title: Blue Cornmeal Pancakes
description: This is a recipe from a cafe in Santa Fe, New Mexico. They are good with maple syrup or, if you're ambitious, with homemade peach or raspberry spread. This recipe serves four people, fewer if they're very hungry.

title: Green Chile Chicken Stew
description: This stew will keep you warm and cozy on those cold winter days!! I got this recipe together after months of harassing my friends in New Mexico in search of the perfect green chile chicken stew. I make it at least once every month (I myself use a pressure cooker). Serve with warm flour tortillas. This recipe has a lot of chile peppers. Be sure to tone it down if you can't handle heat!

title: New Mexico Green Chile Meatloaf
description: New Mexico green chiles set this meatloaf apart if you can find them; serve this sliced for dinner and cold on lunchbox sandwiches tomorrow.

title: Instant Pot® Carne Adovado
description: Chunks of pork shoulder smothered in an easy homemade New Mexico red chile sauce are cooked to succulent tenderness in an Instant Pot®.

title: Creamy Hatch Chile Chicken
description: Stock up on Hatch chiles from New Mexico to make this easy Hatch chile chicken dish with rotisserie chicken, corn, and Mexican crema.

title: Tacos de Alambre
description: This recipe for tacos de alambre is an adaptation of a favorite recipe from a local restaurant in Las Cruces, New Mexico.

title: Melissa's Green Chile Stew
description: A very delicious and satisfying green chile stew with ground beef and potatoes. Especially great with homemade tortillas!

title: Slow Cooker Santa Fe Chicken
description: This Santa Fe chicken recipe is super easy to make in the slow cooker with chicken breasts, canned black beans, tangy salsa, and cream cheese.

title: The Cheesecake Factory Santa Fe Salad
description: Recreate The Cheesecake Factory Santa Fe salad at home with this copycat recipe dressed in a tangy cilantro, lime, and peanut vinaigrette.

title: New Mexican Green Chile Chicken Stew
description: This easy, hearty New Mexican green chile chicken stew is perfect for the colder fall and winter months; it's full of vegetables and flavor.

title: Roasted Green Chile Stew
description: Hearty New Mexico inspired dish that can be made vegetarian simply by omitting the pork. This can be labor intensive and will test your multi-tasking skills if already roasted chiles are not available.

title: Sopapillas
description: This is a flat bread that is easy to prepare, and is usually served with something sweet to put on top, like honey or cinnamon-sugar.

title: Enchiladas - New Mexico Style
description: These enchiladas are stacked like pancakes, not baked in oven. This is a family recipe handed down two generations. Quick, easy and definitely delicious.

title: New Mexico Green Chile Brisket Stew
description: Nicely seasoned beef brisket simmers in an Instant Pot® with pinto beans, carrots, celery, spices, and herbs for a pot of tender and delicious comfort food.

title: Hatch Chile Relleno Casserole with Ranchero Sauce
description: Hatch chiles are New Mexico's gift to the world. Here are layers of Hatch chiles and melted cheese wrapped up in a coat of puffy egg and then baked instead of fried.

title: Santa Fe Carrot Cake
description: Baking at high altitude is easier than ever with this classic recipe for everyone's favorite carrot cake featuring walnuts and raisins.

title: Red Chile Paste
description: The New Mexican dried chiles give this puree its bright red color and the anchos give it a rich, raisiny flavor.

title: Spiced Pumpkin Bread with Raisins and Pecans
description: Fall-inspired spices join pumpkin, raisins, and crunchy pecans in this easy bread that's perfect for the season.

title: Santa Fe Rice Salad
description: This flavorful salad is composed of black beans, rice, fresh tomatoes, Cheddar cheese and green onions dressed with a jalapeno vinaigrette and topped with ripe avocado. Try to use garlic vinegar in the dressing, if you can find it!

title: Instant Pot® Colorado Chile Verde
description: Cooked in the Instant Pot®, this Colorado chile verde recipe is flavored with Hatch chiles and can be served with bread, tortillas, rice, or even over a breakfast burrito!

title: Sizzling Southwest Burgers
description: These zesty burgers are bursting with flavor. Taco seasoning, peppers, and pepperjack cheese give ground beef a boost. Then the patties are served up on buns with sour cream and salsa. A fun twist on barbecued burgers!

title: Hoppin' Juan
description: Give your New Year's Day good-luck dish of black-eyed peas a spicy Southwest flavor with canned hot tomatoes, jalapeno peppers, and bacon.

title: Southwest Chicken Casserole
description: Canned chicken, chiles and soup mix it up with cheese, onion and instant rice in this microwaved casserole.

title: Uncle Jesse's French Toast
description: Super spicy French toast is served up with lots of butter and confectioners' sugar. This recipe comes from my brother's kitchen in New Mexico, he is a great cook.

title: Southwest Squash Casserole
description: Summer squash, onions, peppers, mushrooms and cheese make a great side dish in this easy microwave recipe.

title: Julia's New Mexican Guacamole
description: Full of New Mexico-inspired flavor, this easy chilled guacamole is stuffed with chile peppers, avocados, and cream cheese.

title: Turkey Chorizo (Loose, not Encased)
description: Extra lean turkey is spiced up with chiles, oregano, cumin, and garlic until it tastes just like Mexican chorizo in this homemade sausage recipe.

title: Santa Fe Soup
description: Browned ground beef is combined with processed cheese, onions, tomatoes, corn kernels and cans of ranch-style beans in this easily prepared soup.

title: Linguine with Clam Sauce
description: Linguini with clam sauce is a quick and easy Italian dinner. The garlicky sauce is made with canned clams in butter, oil, parsley, and basil.

title: Scott Ure's Clams And Garlic
description: This garlic butter clams recipe steams little neck clams in a buttery, garlicky white wine broth that's perfect served over pasta with crusty bread.

title: Sautéed Scallops
description: Sautéed scallops in butter with crushed garlic and fresh rosemary; a very simple yet incredibly delicious shellfish main dish for two!

title: Easy Apple Crisp
description: A sweet, crumbly cake mix mixture is spooned over sliced apples and water, and baked in a 9x13-inch pan until the apples are tender and the topping is brown and bubbly.

title: Sweet and Sour Green Beans
description: A slightly tart green bean side dish flavored with onion and bacon. Goes great with ham or pork.

title: Clams Casino
description: Baked, stuffed clams - the best you have ever eaten!

title: Super Summer Grilled Bluefish
description: Have a ton of bluefish and don't know what to do with it? Give this a try! Bluefish has a reputation for being a very strong fish. This super citrus marinade gives this grilled fish a bright and delicious flavor. I just made some (which I caught and froze) and it came out superb.

title: Idaho-Style Finger Steaks
description: This is a highly seasoned, beef nugget just like from the fast food joint of Idaho in the 1970's! Steak strips are soaked in a buttermilk marinade, then breaded in seasoned flour and deep fried.

title: Crab Stuffed Haddock
description: An awesome meal for anytime, and especially impressive to guests yet so simple to make. Haddock fillets are stuffed with a crab and cheese stuffing then baked. A must try - it will be a keeper. Great with salad and rice or potato! Enjoy.

title: Clam Sauce with Linguine
description: This is a super fast and easy recipe. One of my favorites. Linguine is tossed with a buttery clam and mushroom sauce. Fettuccine can also be used. Tastes even better with fresh baked rolls or French bread and a garden salad.

title: Moist Apple Crisp
description: Apples in syrup snuggled between oaty cinnamon-crumble layers and baked.

title: Scallops with White Wine Sauce II
description: White wine, butter, and shallots make a great sauce for scallops. This is easy and non-creamy for those that don't like cream sauces.

title: Berry Cobbler
description: This easy berry cobbler recipe is a perfect dessert. Two cups of your favorite berries are baked for a soft cakey treat. Just mix, pour, bake and eat!

title: Crab Cake Sauce
description: A delicious creamy crab cake sauce that's a breeze to make and tastes great. This recipe makes the perfect complement to lump crab or other seafood.

title: Baked Bluefish
description: This easy baked fish dish tastes delicious served over cooked rice, egg noodles, or on a tossed salad.

title: Haddock Marinara
description: This was my mother's finest fish meal growing up. Even people we know who aren't fish fanatics love this dish. It can be served with rice but we love it with linguine.

title: Chocolate Strawberries
description: Strawberries dipped in melted bittersweet chocolate are simple and elegant.

title: America's Best Barbeque Rub
description: Brown sugar, paprika, hickory smoked salt, and garlic and onion powders make this barbeque rub that goes well on baby back ribs or any meat you grill!

title: Venison with Sherry-Mushroom Sauce
description: Seasoned venison tenderloin steaks are seared then cooked in a sherry-mushroom-sweet onion sauce.

title: Scrumptious Strawberry Shortcake
description: This strawberry shortcake recipe is made from scratch with butter and cream and topped with sugared berries.

title: Spicy Crab Pasta
description: Bow tie pasta is tossed with a buttery crab and tomato sauce. Easy and delicious!

title: Crusted Salmon with Honey-Mustard Sauce
description: Salmon fillets are breaded in Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs and baked before being drizzled with a simple honey-mustard sauce in this tasty recipe.

title: Scrapple (Mush)
description: Scrapple or mush has been a hearty breakfast staple in our family for generations. Heavily flavored with herbs, spices, onions and meat, it is a meal unto itself.

title: Easy Slow Cooker Venison Stew
description: An easy slow cooker stew made with venison and cream of mushroom soup.

title: Annie's Award-Winning Baked Beans
description: This baked bean recipe, made from dried beans, won first place in a baked bean cook-off at the Western Idaho State Fair.

title: Idahoan Molten Lava Cakes
description: This recipe for Molten Lava Cake proves that Idahoan Mashed Potatoes don't have to be saved for just savory applications!

title: Quinoa Chard Pilaf
description: This simple vegan dish combines the distinctive, nutty flavor of quinoa with chard, mushrooms, and lentils. Try using rainbow chard for a colorful effect!

title: Strawberry Soup III
description: Strawberries are blended with buttermilk in this chilled soup sweetened to taste with white sugar.

title: Idaho Fry Sauce
description: This mayonnaise-based fry sauce with tangy seasoning is just what you need to jazz up your french fries. Made with easy ingredients you already have.

title: Clam Fritters
description: My stepmother got this recipe from an 80-year-old woman back in the 1940's.

title: Acorn Squash
description: Learn how to cook acorn squash with this easy recipe. Baking the squash with just butter and brown sugar turns it into a treat everyone will enjoy!

title: Summer Squash Bread
description: This summer squash bread is loaded with a nutritious garden vegetable and flavored with cinnamon, nutmeg, and vanilla for a sweet, tasty brunch dish.

title: Pickled Squash
description: Set some of that abundant summer squash aside for the winter months with this awesome pickled squash recipe.

title: Squash Pie
description: Cooked squash is mixed with hot milk, eggs, butter, sugar, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. When everything is blended perfectly, this luscious filling is poured into a prepared pie shell, and baked in a hot oven until it 's set and golden.

title: Yellow Squash Patties
description: Top these delicious, cheesy squash patties with sour cream and a dash of hot sauce. Everyone will love them!

title: Butternut and Acorn Squash Soup
description: This is a rich and sweet yet surprisingly simple soup that is wonderful served hot with crusty bread or cold with a dollop of sour cream.

title: Easy Barbeque Beef Tenderloin Steak
description: For sensational flavor, rub nice thick tenderloin steaks with olive oil, crushed garlic and meat tenderizer. Let the meat sit for a bit and then grill.

title: Roasted Acorn Squash
description: Roasted acorn squash taste beautiful as-is, but even more so when pan-fried with onions, coriander, nutmeg and garlic. Delicious!

title: Crookneck Squash and Tomatoes
description: Tomatoes and squash are two of the finest things summer has to offer! Enjoy them together in this simple baked side dish.

title: Spicy Fry Sauce
description: In Utah fry sauce is a must with fries. This is a spicy twist to the standard ketchup mayo mixture.

title: Easy Grilled Tri-Tip
description: Slices of beef tri tip are marinated and grilled. This is a great easy summer barbeque idea!

title: Fry Sauce
description: A simple dipping sauce blending the tangy flavors of ketchup and mayonnaise.

title: Caramel Pancake Syrup
description: Brown sugar, light corn syrup, and heavy cream combine in this easy copycat recipe for caramel pancake syrup like they serve at diners.

title: Super Squash
description: A packet of ranch dressing mix adds incredible flavor to this easy summer squash casserole that's topped with a crunchy bread stuffing crust.

title: Mormon Muffins
description: Make bran muffins, Mormon-style, using buttermilk, bran cereal, bran flakes, walnuts, cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.

title: Al's Sufferin' Succotash
description: Frozen lima beans, corn, and green chile peppers cook up quickly for an easy and tasty side dish.

title: Mormon Scalloped Potatoes
description: There's a crunchy, golden topping of buttery corn flakes on top of this classic Utah side dish of creamy scalloped potatoes in a sour cream sauce with green onion.

title: The Best Panna Cotta You Will Ever Have
description: This creamy vanilla-scented panna cotta topped with a juicy blueberry syrup is a make-ahead dessert that will knock your guests' socks off.

title: Mom's Funeral Potatoes
description: Topped with a buttery cornflake topping, these full-of-flavor funeral potatoes made with 2 types of cheese are the ultimate comfort food.

title: Quick Cranberry Pumpkin Muffins
description: Orange zest adds a layer of flavor to these cranberry and pumpkin muffins.

title: Steamed Squash Medley with Sun-Dried Tomatoes
description: Zucchini and yellow squash are steamed with sun-dried tomatoes and sweet onions, and tossed with butter.

title: Sweet Corn Cake
description: A Mexican sweet corn cake recipe with spoonbread consistency. Blend masa harina with cornmeal, sugar, butter and cream in this luscious pudding-cake.

title: Zucchini Nut Bars
description: Another recipe to use up those pesky zucchini, turning your autumnal bounty into bar cookies with walnuts and dates.

title: Idaho Fry Sauce
description: This mayonnaise-based fry sauce with tangy seasoning is just what you need to jazz up your french fries. Made with easy ingredients you already have.

title: Squash Cookies
description: These cookies have a spicy, squash taste. Use any winter squash you like.

title: Perfect Baked Potato
description: This perfect baked potato has a crisp, golden skin, and is light and fluffy on the inside. Add a dollop of sour cream if you like!

title: Slow Cooker Venison Roast
description: This venison roast crockpot dinner couldn't be easier: Venison, onion, and 2 soup mixes simmer in the slow cooker for a creamy, tender, delectable meal.

title: Deer Jerky
description: A deer jerky that's packed with savory flavor and easy to make in the oven with venison marinated in soy sauce, Worcestershire, and liquid smoke.

title: Roasted Duck
description: This roasted duck is coated with a simple, flavorful spice rub, then baked in the oven and basted with butter until tender, juicy, and flavorful.

title: Pan Fried Whole Trout
description: There couldn't be a better way to prepare freshly caught wild brook trout. Serve with a side of creamy mashed potatoes and steamed Swiss chard.

title: Trout Amandine
description: A classic and delicious way to prepare trout.

title: Venison Jerky
description: Make your own venison jerky with ground venison in your dehydrator. This is the best jerky recipe I have found! You can use either ground venison or beef!

title: Venison Schnitzel
description: I don't have a clue where my Dad got this particular recipe, but he used to build it during hunting season when we had fresh venison (elk, antelope, mule or whitetail deer), 'hanging and aging'. I still make it when the opportunity presents itself.

title: Oven Baked Potato Wedges
description: Oven-baked potato wedges are easy and delicious and always a crowd-pleaser. This version of a favorite side is flavored with seasoned bread crumbs.

title: Campfire Trout
description: Seasoned trout is stuffed with green peppers, then rolled up in foil and cooked in the hot coals of a camp fire. Buttery flavor and melt-in-your-mouth texture!

title: Goat Cheese and Arugula over Penne
description: Combine goat cheese with arugula, cherry tomatoes, olive oil, and garlic; toss with hot penne pasta for an absolutely delicious, yet simple summertime dish.

title: Beef or Moose Jerky
description: This beef or moose jerky recipe is smokey, savory, and sweet. Marinate rump roast for rich flavor, then it's done in just 12 hours in a dehydrator.

title: The Humble Shepherd
description: A twist on the original shepherd's pie using ground turkey in place of beef.

title: Easy Slow Cooker Venison Stew
description: An easy slow cooker stew made with venison and cream of mushroom soup.

title: Fennel in Wine and Honey
description: A great side dish for fennel lovers, originally from a friend in Israel. I have used water instead of broth, with some added salt and seasoning. I have also replaced the mustard seed with regular mustard.

title: Spinach and Goat Cheese Salad with Beetroot Vinaigrette
description: A beet vinaigrette is drizzled over baby spinach leaves and walnuts coated with caramelized sugar. Goat cheese brings a final element of distinction to this elegant salad.

title: Montana Russian Black Bread
description: Black bread, made with dark beer, coffee, molasses, and caraway seed, is a hearty Russian-inspired bread perfect for toast, sandwiches, or alongside soup.

title: Cracked Black Venison
description: Tasty and spicy, this is a simple venison steak dish that is easy to make.

title: Montana Spicy Bison Dip
description: Kick off game day with this touchdown-worthy Montana dip, loaded with spicy ground bison meat, fire-roasted tomatoes, and jalapenos.

title: Grandpa Mack's Fifth-Generation Pancake Recipe
description: This family-favorite pancake recipe has been served on a homestead for generations--and it's super quick and easy to prepare.

title: Couscous with Dried Cherries
description: My family loves couscous and this fruity variation is one of our favorites. This is also delicious with other dried fruit such as cranberries and apricots.

title: Jo's Mountain Mush
description: A jumbled, filling breakfast created when I was camping in Montana. Originally the hot dogs were roasted over a fire while the potato pieces were foil wrapped and roasted in the embers and then added into a pan of beans. However, it works equally well when cooked in a kitchen! Serve with crusty bread on the side and fresh shredded cheese on top.
